Raymond J. DOHERTY, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. NEW YORK CENTRAL RAILROAD COMPANY, Defendant-Appellant. No. 73, Docket 23168. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued Oct. 8, 1954. Decided Oct. 8, 1954. Brown, Kelly, Turner & Symons, Buffalo, N. Y. (John E. Leach, Buffalo, N. Y., of counsel), for defendant-appellant. McElroy, Young, Mahley & Dunn, Syracuse, N. Y. (William C. Martin, Syracuse, N. Y., of counsel), for plaintiff-appellee.

Before CLARK, Chief Judge, and L. HAND and FRANK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court.'
